# ---------- SCM push webhooks (Launchpad gitRepoPath — backend) ----------
# Auto-register GitHub/Bitbucket repo webhooks after project gitRepoPath is saved; verify signatures on POST /api/webhooks/*.
# Webhook callbacks use https://{origin}/api/webhooks/... (GitHub/Bitbucket must reach this host). If unset: NGROK_URL → FRONTEND_URL → VITE_FRONTEND_URL → BASE_URL (see backend/src/utils/apiPublicBaseUrl.js). Prefer FRONTEND_URL or VITE_FRONTEND_URL to match the public origin where /api is served (often same as the SPA).
# Random secrets for hook config + HMAC verification (generate: openssl rand -hex 32)
# GITHUB_PUSH_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
# BITBUCKET_PUSH_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
#
# Local webhook testing only (do not set in production; never commit real tokens):
# NGROK_AUTHTOKEN=           # https://dashboard.ngrok.com/get-started/your-authtoken — use with: cd backend && npm run dev:ngrok
# NGROK_URL=                 # optional: manual `ngrok http 5000` + npm start; dev:ngrok sets NGROK_URL automatically
